h1 The Soo

p Our wedding is taking place on Squirrel Island--a remote island located 25 minutes outside of Sault Ste. Marie. The island is accessible by private boat and there are 11 cottages on the island. (No stores, restaurants, etc.) So please bring everything you need with you to the wedding.

h3 Braving the Elements
p Our festivities will take place outdoors and in a tented area. Please bring something warm to wear while on the island. It cools off by the water once the sun goes down. Our wedding will involve boat rides, docks, and a whole lotta lawn (and lawn sports!). For all you heel wearing ladies (and gents), stilettos are probably not ideal unless you get something like these. 

h3 Accommodations
p We’ve reserved a block of rooms at the Holiday Inn Express in downtown Sault Ste. Marie. There are standard rooms available for $110 and suites for $169. The rate includes breakfast. The transportation we have organized to the Island will pick guests up here. 

p Call 1-888-329-7776 and quote “PSW” when booking to receive the discounted rate. We advise booking sooner rather than later as there are limited rooms and the hotels will fill up fast on the long weekend. This rate is only valid until June 30th. 

p When we visited the Soo last fall, we visited a number of hotels and found the Holiday Inn Express to be the nicest, most modern and most affordable. 

p Note: If you look online to try and get a better rate--be sure you aren’t booking a hotel in Sault Ste. Marie, MI. 

h3 Camping
p The night of the wedding, there will be camping available on the island. Bring your own gear. Or let us know way in advance and we might be able to help you find some.
 
h4 Transportation
p Squirrel Island is located near Echo Bay, Ontario—about a 20-minute drive outside of the Soo. On both Saturday and Sunday, we will provide transportation from downtown Sault Ste. Marie to Squirrel Island (and back)

