h3 Getting to the Soo
p Yes. It’s kind of in the middle of nowhere. But that’s the point!
p From Vancouver—Only Air Canada flies direct to Sault Ste. Marie. You must fly through Toronto to get to there. It doesn’t make sense. But that’s just the way it is. 
p If you are flying on Aeroplan points, it’s possible to book a free stopover in Toronto. You have to call them. It won’t work online. It messes with the system because you have to fly east and then west--even the computer knows it doesn’t make any sense. However, if you call them, they can book the stopover for you.

p Sign up here to an email list that will alert you to seat sales as they come up!
p Porter also flies to Sault Ste. Marie from downtown Toronto.  If you are considering spending some time in Toronto before heading to the Soo, this is a good option as there are often great sales. And there is free wine. (Yes, that’s right. FREE WINE!)
p To get to Sault Ste. Marie from the airport--the best option is a six-person taxi. It’s a flat rate of $30. 

